<h2>2. Login</h2>
<p>Use Http Authentication to login and expose user's API token, which is required for some actions.</p>

<h3>Request</h3>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Method</th>
            <th>URL</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>POST</td>
            <td>/api/v1/sessions</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Params</th>
            <th>Type</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>username</td>
            <td>string</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>password</td>
            <td>string</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Response</h3>
<p>api_token exposed after login needs to be added to header for future authenticated actions.</p>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Status</th>
            <th>Response</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>200</td>
            <td>{<br>
                "token": "(api_token)"<br>
            }</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>401</td>
            <td>Unauthorized: Invalid credentials</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

